  "prompt": "Has anyone survived a plane crash?",
  "response": "Yes, there have been several instances where people have survived plane crashes. While plane crashes are often fatal, survival is possible depending on various factors such as the severity of the crash, the location of the accident, and the response of the passengers and crew. Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **Juliane Koepcke** - In 1971, Juliane Koepcke was the sole survivor of LANSA Flight 508, which crashed in the Peruvian rainforest. She survived an 11-day ordeal in the jungle before being rescued.\n\n2. **Cecelia Cichan** - In 1987, Cecelia Cichan was the only survivor of Northwest Airlines Flight 255, which crashed shortly after takeoff in Detroit, Michigan. She was just four years old at the time.\n\n3. **Bahia Bakari** - In 2009, Bahia Bakari was the sole survivor of Yemenia Flight 626, which crashed into the Indian Ocean. She floated in the water for over 13 hours before being rescued.\n\n4. **George Lamson Jr.** - In 1985, George Lamson Jr. was one of two survivors of Galaxy Airlines Flight 203, which crashed in Reno, Nevada. He was 17 years old at the time.\n\n5. **Audrey Decker** - In 2008, Audrey Decker survived the crash of First Air Flight 6560 in Resolute Bay, Canada. She was one of 12 survivors out of 15 people on board.\n\nThese cases highlight the resilience of the human spirit and the importance of survival training and safety measures in aviation. While surviving a plane crash is rare, it is not impossible.",
